Four more suspects have been arrested arrested in connection with a robbery which allegedly happened in Ngcobo December last year. The were arrested by the Task Team investigating the Ngcobo police killings in the Eastern Cape. Provincial Hawks spokesperson Anelisa Feni says the four have joined six others who have been arrested in relation to the crime. This brings to 10 the number of suspects arrested and charged with conspiracy to commit robbery with aggravating circumstances. Feni says, “These three were arrested in Dutywa and one was arrested in Mthatha. These arrests are in relation to the December 2017 robbery which allegedly occurred in Ngcobo. It is alleged that the four committed this crime while they were residing at the Seven Angels Ministries.” Click below for a related video:  About Fundiswa Mhlekude View all posts by Fundiswa Mhlekude